excerpt: Museum with kitschy oddities on display, including shrunken human heads & rare animal skeletons.
detail_description: Ripley's Believe It Or Not is a museum that has been captivating visitors for over 90 years with its extraordinary attractions in 10 countries. The outpost at Wisconsin Dells boasts three floors of exhibits and illusions, featuring 11 galleries filled with oddities and curiosities. Visitors can explore ancient artifacts in the Temple of Discovery and experience mind-boggling illusions throughout the dimly lit facility.
name: Ripley's Believe It Or Not
address: 105 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: 70-acre family water park with both thrill & child-friendly slides, lazy rivers, wave pools & more.
detail_description: Noah's Ark Waterpark is a sprawling 70-acre family-friendly destination in Wisconsin Dells, known as America's largest waterpark. With over 51 water slides, the park offers a wide range of attractions suitable for all ages. From thrilling tube slides like The Plunge and Monkey Rapids to leisurely options such as lazy rivers and wave pools, there's something for everyone. Special areas are designated for kids, ensuring they have a safe and enjoyable experience.
name: Noah's Ark Waterpark
address: 1410 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: 40-acre family-friendly petting zoo featuring a variety of deer plus elk, bison & other wildlife.
detail_description: Wisconsin Deer Park is a 40-acre petting zoo that has been operating for over fifty years. It offers visitors the opportunity to interact with and feed over 100 deer, as well as other wildlife such as elk, bison, goats, lemurs, and llamas. The park's well-groomed trails provide an authentic experience where guests can get up close and personal with the animals while learning about their life cycles.
name: Wisconsin Deer Park
address: 2183 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Landmark restored photography studio featuring history exhibits, photos & recreated workspaces.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Wisconsin Dells, H. H. Bennett Studio stands as a remarkable tribute to the legacy of Henry Hamilton Bennett, a trailblazing photographer who played a pivotal role in showcasing the area's stunning landscapes. Established in 1875, this historic studio is not only the oldest operating business in town but also serves as an engaging museum filled with fascinating exhibits that delve into both Bennett's life and his artistic contributions.
name: H. H. Bennett Studio
address: 215 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Professional magicians deliver live comedic entertainment, with souvenirs available.
detail_description: The Rick Wilcox Magic Theater, located in Wisconsin Dells, is a 550-seat theater opened by master illusionists Rick and Suzan Wilcox in 1999. The 90-minute show features a blend of magic, comedy, and quick wit that keeps the audience entertained and amazed. After the show, guests have the opportunity to meet the gracious hosts for autographs and photos. This unique entertainment experience is constantly updated with new tricks and techniques to ensure an unforgettable evening of grand illusions.
name: Rick Wilcox Magic Theater
address: 1670 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Long-running water-ski & boat show featuring extreme stunts & comedy during the summer.
detail_description: The Tommy Bartlett Exploratory is a must-see attraction at the Polynesian Water Park Resort during the summer. Known as the Greatest Show on H2O, this long-running water-ski and boat show features thrilling stunts and comedy routines that captivate audiences. The 90-minute show includes impressive water-skiing performances, daring boat stunts, and entertaining comedy acts.
name: Tommy Bartlett Exploratory
address: 560 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Tranquil, 144-acre park with campsites & hiking trails amid pine-tree forests & sandstone bluffs.
detail_description: Rocky Arbor State Park is a serene 144-acre park nestled in pine-tree forests and sandstone bluffs. It may be smaller than nearby Mirror Lake State Park, but it offers stunning scenery with a 1-mile trail winding through a beautiful sandstone gorge. The park features a campground with 89 sites, including some with electrical hookups, modern amenities like restrooms and showers, making it an ideal spot for camping between Memorial Day and Labor Day.
name: Rocky Arbor State Park
address: N101 US Hwy. 12 and 16, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: The Original Wisconsin Ducks is a must-visit attraction in Wisconsin Dells, offering unique tours on amphibious vehicles that date back to World War II. The tour takes visitors through the picturesque Lake Delton and Wisconsin River, providing interesting insights about the environment and the city.
name: Original Wisconsin Ducks
address: 1890 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: Mt. Olympus - Water & Theme Park Resort is the world's largest water resort, featuring 37 waterslides, 3 lazy rivers, and 2 massive wave pools. The theme park is designed around Ancient Greece and Greek mythology, offering roller coasters, outdoor water slides, and go-karts that pass through underwater tunnels. With a variety of accommodations including budget-friendly hotel rooms and a Camp Resort with cabins and tent sites, this resort provides an adventurous experience for all ages.
name: Mt. Olympus - Water & Theme Park Resort
address: 1701 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy A, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Family-friendly museum with old-fashioned train rides, locomotives on display & a gift shop.
detail_description: The Riverside & Great Northern Railway is a delightful destination for families and train enthusiasts alike, offering an enchanting blend of history and adventure. Located along N115 County Road N, this living museum showcases the preservation of locomotives and passenger cars crafted by the Sandley Light Railway Equipment Works from 1950 to 1980. Visitors can embark on scenic steam train rides that traverse a picturesque three-mile route through lush woodlands and stunning canyons alongside the Wisconsin River.
name: Riverside & Great Northern Railway
address: N115 County Rd N, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: Riverwalk in Wisconsin Dells offers a peaceful escape from the bustling Broadway Avenue. The half-mile paved pathway provides stunning views of the Wisconsin River and its sandstone cliffs, previously inaccessible to the public until 2003. Along the route, visitors can learn about the town's history and natural beauty through informational signs. The walkway also features game tables and benches for relaxation.
name: Riverwalk
address: 105 Broadway #91, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: Dells Boat Tours is a well-established tour operator offering scenic cruises along the Wisconsin River, showcasing the area's unique rock formations. With tours running from mid-April to early November, visitors can choose between exploring the Upper Dells or Lower Dells. The Upper Dells tour includes access to Witches Gulch and Stand Rock, where a trained dog performs a cliff leap. On the other hand, Lower Dells Boat Tours cruise downstream.
name: Dells Boat Tours
address: 107 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Complex with 5 unique mini-golf courses plus a giant chess board, water play area & pedal carts.
detail_description: Pirate's Cove Adventure Golf is a family-friendly destination in Wisconsin Dells, offering five distinct mini-golf courses and a range of attractions. From the easiest course, Blackbeard's 18, to the medium difficulty Pirates Lookout, visitors can enjoy challenging their golf skills while surrounded by stunning landscapes and water features. The complex boasts 91 holes in total and provides amenities such as picnic shelters with barbecue grills for a relaxing day out.
name: Pirate's Cove Adventure Golf
address: 193 U.S, State Hwy 13, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: Located in downtown Wisconsin Dells, Carr Valley Cheese Co Inc is a must-visit attraction for cheese enthusiasts. The cheese factory offers a wide selection of cheeses, including award-winning varieties available for sampling. Visitors can also explore an assortment of salsa and spreads. The store boasts fair prices, excellent customer service, and a clean, inviting atmosphere. Additionally, the establishment has garnered praise for its vegan-based restaurant that serves non-GMO organic food.
name: Carr Valley Cheese Co Inc
address: 420 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Long gorge, formed during last ice age, where boaters can observe rock formations & cliffs by boat.
detail_description: Dells of the Wisconsin River State Natural Area is a stunning gorge formed during the last ice age, offering visitors the chance to observe rock formations and cliffs by boat. The Chapel Gorge Trail provides an easy 1.5-mile trek through dense hardwood forest, leading to a secluded beach where picnickers and paddlers relax along the shoreline.
name: Dells of the Wisconsin River State Natural Area
address: Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Animal park with giraffes, monkeys, tigers & more, plus exhibits, shows & interactive activities.
detail_description: Timbavati Wildlife Park is a family-friendly animal park that has been around for centuries and is home to over 350 animals from more than 70 species. Visitors can enjoy supervised interaction with various animals throughout the park and even take a ride on the Safari Train or a trained camel. The park offers interactive activities such as camel and pony rides, as well as opportunities for children to have close encounters with baby wallabies and kangaroos.
name: Timbavati Wildlife Park
address: 2220 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Cash-only drive-in movie theater offering first-run features on 2 screens, plus concessions.
detail_description: Experience a blast from the past at Big Sky Twin Drive-In Theater, a cash-only movie spot in Wisconsin Dells. This classic drive-in offers first-run features on two screens and a concession stand with various snacks. Originally opened in the 1950s as Winnebago Drive-In, it now accommodates around 400 cars for double features. Enjoy the nostalgia of watching movies from your car at affordable prices - $10 for adults and $5 for kids (cash only).
name: Big Sky Twin Drive-In Theater
address: N9199 Winnebago Rd, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

detail_description: If you're looking for a thrilling indoor adventure in Wisconsin Dells, look no further than Wild Fun Zone! This vibrant attraction is packed with excitement, featuring an impressive array of activities that cater to all ages. From the area's largest indoor laser tag arena to exhilarating bumper cars and a unique 3D black light mini golf experience, there's something for everyone.
name: Wild Fun Zone
address: 310 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Attraction where visitors search a maze & are asked riddles & questions to help find hidden wizards.
detail_description: Wizard Quest is a popular tourist attraction in Wisconsin Dells, offering a unique and immersive experience for visitors. Spanning 13,000 square feet, this theme park takes participants through interactive gaming challenges and fantasy scenarios. Visitors can pick up a wand and use its magic to navigate through whimsical structures and fantastical settings while solving riddles to uncover hidden passages within themed areas such as water, wind, earth, and fire.
name: Wizard Quest
address: 400 Broadway, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA

excerpt: Easygoing, modern coffee shop for caffeinated sips & smoothies plus biscuits, baked goods & waffles.
detail_description: Nestled along the scenic Wisconsin River, Bella Goose Coffee - Cafe on the River is a delightful haven for coffee lovers and brunch enthusiasts alike. This modern coffee shop offers an inviting atmosphere where you can savor expertly roasted brews, refreshing smoothies, and a tempting array of baked goods like their famous oatmeal cookies.
name: Bella Goose Coffee - Cafe on the River
address: 2370 Wisconsin Dells Pkwy, Wisconsin Dells, WI 53965, USA
